SUMMARY:The Music Man
DESCRIPTION:Seventy-six trombones. One unforgettable musical!\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Meredith WillsonтАЩs six-time Tony Award┬о-winning beloved musical comedy The Music Man marches into Houston with laughter\, heart\, and all the music you love. Following the fast-talking traveling salesman Harold Hill as he cons the people of River City\, Iowa\, into buying instruments and uniforms for a boysтАЩ band that he vows to organize. Featuring songs such as тАЬSeventy-Six Trombones\,тАЭ тАЬTrouble\,тАЭ тАЬтАЩTill There Was You\,тАЭ тАЬPick-a-Little\,тАЭ and тАЬGary\, Indiana\,тАЭ The Music Man is a classic musical to be shared with every generation. \n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				CRITICAL ACCLAIM FOR THE MUSIC MAN\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n					тАУ The Telegraph \n					\n					тАЬA joyous\, blissful Broadway event!тАЭ \n					\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n					тАУ Variety \n					\n					тАЬGrand and Glorious!тАЭ тАЬтАжtotally enchanting abso-tootinтАЩ-lutely smashing revival. It will give you new life.тАЭ \n					\n				\n				\n			\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				PERFORMANCE SCHEDULE\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФTuesday\, Sept 15\, 7:30 p.m. тАУ H-E-B Community Night\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФWednesday\, Sept 16\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФThursday\, Sept 17\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФFriday\, Sept 18\, 8 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSaturday\, Sept 19\, 2 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSaturday\, Sept 19\, 8 p.m.\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSunday\, Sept 20\, 2 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSunday\, Sept 20\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФTuesday\, Sept 22\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФWednesday\, Sept 23\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФThursday\, Sept 24\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФFriday\, Sept 25\, 8 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSaturday\, Sept 26\, 2 p.m. тАФ Open Captioned \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSaturday\, Sept 26\, 8 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				яБФSunday\, Sept 27\, 2 p.m. тАФ ASL & Audio Described \n			\n				\n			\n				SUBSCRIBE NOW\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				TICKETING INFO\nSeason tickets are now available.┬а6-show packages start at just $34 per-show. \nTickets will start at $46 and will be available beginning July 13 online or by calling TUTS Guest Services at 713-558-8887. Tickets will also available in person Monday through Friday from Noon to 6 p.m. at the TUTS Box Office\, located in the Hobby Center lobby. \nDiscounted group tickets are available for parties of 10 or more.Theatre Under The Stars has a variety of accessibility options for guests.Learn more about accessible performances and other services here. \nRush tickets will be available for $35 at the box office for mezzanine and gallery seating starting 2 hours prior to curtain. \nQuestions about parking\, dining or other aspects of attending a TUTS show? WeтАЩve got answers! \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				RUN TIME\n2 hours and 30 minutes including intermission\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Photos\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n                \n                    \n                    