SUMMARY:Oh\, Mary!
DESCRIPTION:History has never been this unhinged.\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Oh\, Mary! is a dark comedy about a miserable\, suffocated Mary Todd Lincoln in the weeks leading up to Abraham LincolnтАЩs assassination. Unrequited yearning\, alcoholism\, and suppressed desires abound in this 80-minute one-act play that finally examines the forgotten life and dreams of Mrs. Lincoln\, through the lens of an idiot (playwright Cole Escola). \nDeclared тАЬone of the best comedies in yearsтАЭ by The New York Times\, Oh\, Mary! received two Tony Awards┬о including Best Direction of a Play (Sam Pinkleton)\, Drama League Awards for Outstanding Play and Outstanding Direction of a Play\, as well as a special citation from the New York Drama CriticsтАЩ Circle. It was named a finalist for the Pulitzer Prize for Drama. \n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Cole Escola in Oh\, Mary! on Broadway. Photo by Emilio Madrid. \n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				CRITICAL ACCLAIM FOR OH\, MARY!\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n					тАФThe New York Times\, CriticтАЩs Pick\n					\n					тАЬYouтАЩll be losing your mind with joy.тАЭ \n					\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n					тАФThe Hollywood Reporter\n					\n					тАЬ80 minutes of almost uninterrupted laughter. A work of genius.тАЭ \n					\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\n					тАФDeadline\n					\n					тАЬThereтАЩs funny\, thereтАЩs very funny\, and then thereтАЩs Oh\, Mary!тАЭ \n					\n				\n				\n			\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n		